abstract: The New York State Senate is letting an effective traffic-safety program die.
snippet: The New York State Senate is letting an effective traffic-safety program die.
lead_paragraph: For all of the attention that offenses like D.U.I.s, road rage and texting-while-driving rightly receive, the biggest threat to traffic safety on New York City’s streets is the State Senate.

headline_main: Why Would We Sacrifice Safety at New York City Schools?
byline_original: By Janette Sadik-Khan and Lucius J. Riccio

abstract: New York City has built more than 70 pedestrian plazas in the last 10 years as a way to improve traffic flow. To many, they look like parks in the street.
snippet: New York City has built more than 70 pedestrian plazas in the last 10 years as a way to improve traffic flow. To many, they look like parks in the street.
lead_paragraph: A decade ago, when Dr. Pezhman Hourizadeh opened his optometry practice in Corona, Queens, his storefront faced a street that was only a block long and mainly served as a parking lot for vans from nearby moving companies. “Patients who came by in cars couldn’t come in,” he recalled.

abstract: Andy Byford met with Mayor Bill de Blasio for the first time on Tuesday, nearly six months after he arrived to fix the system.
snippet: Andy Byford met with Mayor Bill de Blasio for the first time on Tuesday, nearly six months after he arrived to fix the system.
lead_paragraph: For nearly six months, the mayor of New York City did not meet with the man responsible for fixing his city’s failing subway. In fact, Mayor Bill de Blasio had not even spoken with Andy Byford, the subway’s leader, since Mr. Byford arrived in New York in January.

abstract: A week after a newsroom shooting killed five, journalists from around the country have gone to Maryland to work with the depleted staff.
snippet: A week after a newsroom shooting killed five, journalists from around the country have gone to Maryland to work with the depleted staff.
lead_paragraph: Newspapers around the country are offering support to the Baltimore Sun Media Group, the owner of the Capital Gazette chain of community newspapers based in Annapolis, Md., in the wake of a newsroom shooting that killed five employees.

headline_main: DealBook Briefing: Merger Binge Could Lead to a Hangover

abstract: Being left out when Mayor Bill de Blasio announced a plan to change admissions to the city’s elite high schools, where they dominate, was only the last straw, leaders say.
snippet: Being left out when Mayor Bill de Blasio announced a plan to change admissions to the city’s elite high schools, where they dominate, was only the last straw, leaders say.
lead_paragraph: When Mayor Bill de Blasio proposed a change in the way students are admitted to the city’s most elite public high schools, he was surrounded by dozens of enthusiastic students, union leaders and elected officials, amid signs proclaiming “All Kids Deserve a Chance.”
